37: /**
38:  * A range assignor assigns contiguous partition ranges to members of a consumer group such that:
39:  * <ol>
40:  *   <li>Each subscribed member receives at least one partition from that topic.</li>
41:  *   <li>Each member receives the same partition number from every subscribed topic when co-partitioning is possible.</li>
42:  * </ol>
43:  *
44:  * Co-partitioning is possible when the below conditions are satisfied:
45:  * <ol>
46:  *   <li>All the members are subscribed to the same set of topics.</li>
47:  *   <li>All the topics have the same number of partitions.</li>
48:  * </ol>
49:  *
50:  * Co-partitioning is useful in performing joins on data streams.
